# Values you supply PER MACHINE. This file just documents what each server needs —
# the installer PROMPTS for each at install time and writes it straight into
# Claude's config. Nothing is committed to this repo.
#
# You do NOT need to fill this file in; it's a reference.

# ── teamwork ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# TW_MCP_BEARER_TOKEN  (secret) — Teamwork API bearer token.
#   Mint with:  npx -y @teamwork/get-bearer-token@latest
# TW_MCP_API_URL       — your Teamwork site, e.g. https://<your-site>.teamwork.com

# ── ms365 / outlook ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Your own Azure AD app registration (public client; "Allow public client flows" = Yes):
# MS365_MCP_CLIENT_ID            — the app (client) ID of your Azure app reg
# SIMPLY_OUTLOOK_MCP_CLIENT_ID   — same app (client) ID, for the Outlook server
# (Not secret, but machine/org-specific — the installer asks for them; nothing is hard-coded.)
#
# ms365 is installed ONCE PER ACCOUNT. Each install asks for:
#   • a 4-letter prefix → names the MCP  ms365-<prefix>  (tool namespace)
#   • tenant (optional) → MS365_MCP_TENANT_ID; Enter = 'common' (work/school),
#     'consumers' for a personal Microsoft account (else its session dies ~1h after login)
# Per-account tokens are saved under servers/ms365/.creds/<prefix>/ (git-ignored),
# not the keychain, so multiple accounts stay isolated.

# ── Servers that authenticate interactively (nothing to paste) ──
# ms365     : per account, run  ./servers/ms365/login.sh <prefix>  (device-code; token in .creds/<prefix>/)
# readai    : run  uv run servers/readai/auth.py  (browser OAuth)
# telegram  : paste API id/hash + a session string at the prompt (no phone login if reusing a session string)
# whatsapp  : scan the QR code the bridge prints on first run
# outlook   : OAuth on first use (uses your ms365 Azure app)
